  "text": "Veneri et al. reported that the host factors HLADRB111, HLA-DRB 114, and HLA-DQB 103 occurred at high frequencies in patients with H. pylori-positive ITP, while the frequency of the host factor HLA-DRB 103 was higher in the H. pylori-negative ITP group than in the H. pylori-positive ITP group. HLA-DQB 103 showed favorable platelet reactivity after H. pylori eradication therapy in H. pylori-positive ITP patients. [CITATION_1] ",
